Online Exercise - Topic 3: Wordcloud to analyze tweets

Introduction to R FS 20 UZH

Tobias Boner 17-707-878

In this R notebook we will provide a step by step guide to create a wordcloud. Therefore, we use the wordcloud() function to analyze tweets (corona_tweets.csv)

This work will adress the following points:

  1. What is the reason for plotting a word cloud representing Tweets?
  2. What are the steps in plotting Tweets?
    • List and explain the specific steps to prepare the input data.
    • Explain your reasoning for all steps, e.g.subsetting the data, creating new variables, manipulating data structures.
    • Which variables do you include and why?
    • Make sure the graph makes sense and is visually appealing (i.e.remove irrelevant words, coloring of important words).
  3. Show and interpret the word cloud you created.
  4. Summary

Step 1:

Load and (install > only needed once) all nececessary packages

### load packages ###
library(data.table)
library(lubridate)
library(wordcloud)
library(RColorBrewer)
library(wordcloud2)

# shows you all installed packages
installed.packages()

Step 2:

#####load the data that entails the tweets ######

data <- fread("corona_tweets.csv")
